  "poem": {
    "content": "The leaves fall, a kingdom’s edge, a brittle grace,\nWhere dreams recycle, chasing yesterday's trace.\nA wish unspoken, shy behind the fringe,\nAlpha whispers where the wild winds cringe.\n\nDrama unfolds, a show upon the sand,\nTwice measured steps upon the shifting land.\nThe runway beckons, a path not meant for me,\nA hockey game of souls, for all eternity.\n\nI shoot a glance towards that fading light,\nAcross the border, blurring day and night.\nA space to try to just be alive,\nA chance to feel like you could still thrive.\n\nI recycle tears for all I couldn't be,\nThose fallen days I'd hoped so I could see.\nWe fall again, a slow and silent bend,\nWhere futures fray and all the stories end.",
